Description: clipboard time machine - searchable clipboard history
 deja records everything you copy into a local SQLite database and makes
 it instantly searchable from the command line or a GTK4 popup.
 .
 A lightweight daemon watches the clipboard (event-driven on Wayland,
 polling on X11), deduplicates entries, and prunes old history. Entries
 can be pinned, restored to the clipboard, or purged. Content flagged by
 password managers is never recorded, and recording can be paused at any
 time. All data stays on the local machine.
